    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a vertically aligned hollow cone with its narrow end pointing downward. The bottom of the cone is cut off as it touches a horizontal surface, and the angle between the side of the cone and the horizontal is theta sub 0. A coin is located inside the cone in contact with the inside surface, and the radius of the cone at the location of the coin inside the cone is r sub 0. A pair of axes shows that the horizontal axis is the x-axis and the vertical axis is the y-axis.\" src=\"/images/246ad1681d494466b351ea03d758be17.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A coin rolls with constant speed <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v sub 0\"><math alttext=\"v sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> in a circular path along the inside surface of a cone, as shown. The radius of curvature of the coin’s path is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r sub 0\"><math alttext=\"r sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> and the surface of the cone is at an angle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 0\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> to the horizontal. The coin is then moved to another cone whose surface is at an angle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 1\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> such that <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the tangent of theta sub 1, equals 9 times the tangent of theta sub 0\"><math alttext=\"the tangent of theta sub 1, equals 9 times the tangent of theta sub 0\" display=\"inline